ZCZC GE65
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD START WITH A WEAK RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE LYING ALIGNED
N-S OVER THE UK WITH HIGH PRESSURE DOMINATING THE CONTINENT. AT THE SAME
TIME A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP IN THE NEAR N ATLANTIC WITH CENTRAL
PRESSURE NEAR 990. THE RIDGE IS EXP TO SOON DECLINE OVER THE UK AS THE MAIN
LOW MOVS S AND THEN E TOWARDS UK AND IRELAND PROBABLY COMING TO LIE OFF
NWERN SCOTLAND TO END THE FOUR DAYS WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE NEAR 995. BY THIS
TIME HIGH PRESSURE SHOULD REMAIN IN FORCE OVER MUCH OF MAINLAND WERN EUROPE.
A SWATHE OF STRG WINDS MAY MOV BODILY EWARDS ACROSS NERN CULLERCOATS ON THURSDAY
PERHAPS GIVING WAY TO A MORE PREVALENT SWATHE IN THE NW INTO FRIDAY ELSE
